com.solidfire.element.api

Class Snapshot

  • Object
    • Snapshot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Snapshot
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Snapshot Snapshots is an object containing information about each snapshot made for a volume. The return object includes information for the active snapshot as well as each snapshot created for the volume.

        public Optional<SnapshotRemoteStatus[]> getRemoteStatuses()
        Current remote status of the snapshot remoteStatus: Possible values: Present: Snapshot exists on a remote cluster Not Present: Snapshot does not exist on remote cluster Syncing: This is a target cluster and it is currently replicating the snapshot Deleted: This is a target cluster, the snapshot has been deleted, and it still exists on the source. volumePairUUID: universal identifier of the volume pair
